user|`{{.Func}}` returns wrong values when input slice is empty. Repro?
ai|Looks like an off-by-one. The loop probably runs from 0 to len-1 but you index `result[i+1]` somewhere. Mind sharing the body?
user|Yeah it's `for i := range items { result[i+1] = items[i] }`.
ai|There it is. When items is empty the slice stays untouched, but when it has 1 element you write to index 1 of a 1-len slice — panic. Initialize `result` with `len(items)+1` or change the index expression.
user|Initializing larger fixed it.
